---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";

const title = "FAQ";
---

<Layout title={title}>
  <main
    class="prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-5xl mx-auto px-5 pt-28 pb-10"
  >
    <h1 class="text-center">Frequently Asked Questions</h1>

    <div class="not-prose">
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <details class="group bg-dark-gray rounded-lg" open>
          <summary
            class="flex cursor-pointer items-center justify-between gap-1.5 p-4 text-gray-900"
          >
            <h2 class="font-medium text-gray-100">
              How do I get started with Blankie?
            </h2>
            <svg
              class="h-5 w-5 shrink-0 transition duration-300 group-open:-rotate-180 stroke-gray-100"
              xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
              fill="none"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              stroke-width="1.5"
            >
              <path
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                d="M19.5 8.25l-7.5 7.5-7.5-7.5"></path>
            </svg>
          </summary>

          <div class="p-4 pt-0 text-gray-300">
            <p class="mb-4">There's currently two ways to get started:</p>
            <ol class="list-decimal pl-6 space-y-4">
              <li>
                <span class="font-semibold block mb-2">TestFlight</span>
                Get early access to new features by joining our
                <a
                  href="https://testflight.apple.com/join/XgpBpWv8"
                  class="text-yellow-500 hover:text-yellow-700 transition-colors"
                  >TestFlight Public Beta</a
                >
              </li>
              <li>
                <span class="font-semibold block mb-2">Direct Download</span>
                <ol class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
                  <li>
                    Download the latest .zip from the <a
                      href="https://github.com/codybrom/blankie/releases"
                      class="text-yellow-500 hover:text-yellow-700 transition-colors"
                      >Releases</a
                    > on GitHub
                  </li>
                  <li>Copy the app to your Applications folder</li>
                  <li>Open Blankie and click a sound to start!</li>
                </ol>
              </li>
            </ol>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group bg-dark-gray rounded-lg">
          <summary
            class="flex cursor-pointer items-center justify-between gap-1.5 p-4 text-gray-900"
          >
            <h2 class="font-medium text-gray-100">Is Blankie free?</h2>
            <svg
              class="h-5 w-5 shrink-0 transition duration-300 group-open:-rotate-180 stroke-gray-100"
              xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
              fill="none"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              stroke-width="1.5"
            >
              <path
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                d="M19.5 8.25l-7.5 7.5-7.5-7.5"></path>
            </svg>
          </summary>

          <div class="p-4 pt-0 text-gray-300">
            <p class="mb-4">
              Yes! Blankie is completely free (and open source!). You can
              download and use Blankie at no cost, forever.
            </p>
            <p class="mb-4">
              We believe everyone should have access to tools that help them
              focus, relax, and be productive. Blankie is developed and
              maintained as a passion project supported by an amazing open
              source community.
            </p>
            <p>
              While Blankie will always remain free, if you'd like to support
              development you can:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mt-2">
              <li>
                Star and contribute to the project on <a
                  href="https://github.com/codybrom/blankie"
                  class="text-yellow-500 hover:text-yellow-700 transition-colors"
                  >GitHub</a
                >
              </li>
              <li>Help test new features through TestFlight</li>
              <li>Share Blankie with others who might find it useful</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group bg-dark-gray rounded-lg">
          <summary
            class="flex cursor-pointer items-center justify-between gap-1.5 p-4 text-gray-900"
          >
            <h2 class="font-medium text-gray-100">
              How do I control playback and volume?
            </h2>
            <svg
              class="h-5 w-5 shrink-0 transition duration-300 group-open:-rotate-180 stroke-gray-100"
              xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
              fill="none"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              stroke-width="1.5"
            >
              <path
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                d="M19.5 8.25l-7.5 7.5-7.5-7.5"></path>
            </svg>
          </summary>

          <div class="p-4 pt-0 text-gray-300">
            <p class="mb-4">
              <span class="font-semibold">Play/Pause:</span> The main play/pause
              button at the bottom center controls all selected sounds simultaneously.
              You can also:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 mb-4">
              <li>Use media keys on your keyboard</li>
              <li>Control from the Now Playing widget in your menubar</li>
              <li>
                Control directly from AirPods and other compatible headphones
              </li>
            </ul>
            <div>
              <p class="font-semibold mb-2">Volume:</p>
              <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
                <li>Use individual sliders for each sound</li>
                <li>
                  Access the global volume slider from the controls bar (speaker
                  icon) to blend with other apps
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group bg-dark-gray rounded-lg">
          <summary
            class="flex cursor-pointer items-center justify-between gap-1.5 p-4 text-gray-900"
          >
            <h2 class="font-medium text-gray-100">
              Can I save my favorite sound combinations?
            </h2>
            <svg
              class="h-5 w-5 shrink-0 transition duration-300 group-open:-rotate-180 stroke-gray-100"
              xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
              fill="none"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              stroke-width="1.5"
            >
              <path
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                d="M19.5 8.25l-7.5 7.5-7.5-7.5"></path>
            </svg>
          </summary>

          <div class="p-4 pt-0 text-gray-300">
            <p class="mb-2">
              Yes! Presets store active sounds and their volume levels. You can
              save and load different combinations as presets. If you don't have
              any presets saved, Blankie will load whatever sounds were active
              when you last closed the app.
            </p>
            <p class="mb-2">
              To save a preset, click the "Presets" dropdown in the titlebar,
              and then click "New Preset". When you create your first preset,
              Blankie will automatically copy your current sound settings to it.
              Any changes you make to an active preset's sounds or volumes are
              saved immediately. There's no need to manually save your changes.
            </p>
            <p>
              To rename or delete a preset, click the "Presets" dropdown in the
              titlebar, and then click either the pencil or trash icon next to
              the preset you want to edit.
            </p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group bg-dark-gray rounded-lg">
          <summary
            class="flex cursor-pointer items-center justify-between gap-1.5 p-4 text-gray-900"
          >
            <h2 class="font-medium text-gray-100">Can I add my own sounds?</h2>
            <svg
              class="h-5 w-5 shrink-0 transition duration-300 group-open:-rotate-180 stroke-gray-100"
              xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
              fill="none"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              stroke-width="1.5"
            >
              <path
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                d="M19.5 8.25l-7.5 7.5-7.5-7.5"></path>
            </svg>
          </summary>

          <div class="p-4 pt-0 text-gray-300">
            <p>
              Not yet, but custom sound support is planned for a future update.
              Follow our GitHub repository for updates!
            </p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group bg-dark-gray rounded-lg">
          <summary
            class="flex cursor-pointer items-center justify-between gap-1.5 p-4 text-gray-900"
          >
            <h2 class="font-medium text-gray-100">
              What customization options are available?
            </h2>
            <svg
              class="h-5 w-5 shrink-0 transition duration-300 group-open:-rotate-180 stroke-gray-100"
              xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
              fill="none"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              stroke-width="1.5"
            >
              <path
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                d="M19.5 8.25l-7.5 7.5-7.5-7.5"></path>
            </svg>
          </summary>

          <div class="p-4 pt-0 text-gray-300">
            <ul class="list-disc pl-5">
              <li>Hide inactive sounds for a cleaner interface</li>
              <li>Use keyboard shortcuts for quick access to main functions</li>
              <li>
                Customize appearance and auto-start settings in Preferences
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group bg-dark-gray rounded-lg">
          <summary
            class="flex cursor-pointer items-center justify-between gap-1.5 p-4 text-gray-900"
          >
            <h2 class="font-medium text-gray-100">
              Where can I find keyboard shortcuts?
            </h2>
            <svg
              class="h-5 w-5 shrink-0 transition duration-300 group-open:-rotate-180 stroke-gray-100"
              xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
              fill="none"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              stroke-width="1.5"
            >
              <path
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                d="M19.5 8.25l-7.5 7.5-7.5-7.5"></path>
            </svg>
          </summary>

          <div class="p-4 pt-0 text-gray-300">
            <p>
              Access the full list of keyboard shortcuts from the "Keyboard
              Shortcuts" panel in the Titlebar menu.
            </p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group bg-dark-gray rounded-lg">
          <summary
            class="flex cursor-pointer items-center justify-between gap-1.5 p-4 text-gray-900"
          >
            <h2 class="font-medium text-gray-100">
              How do I access Preferences?
            </h2>
            <svg
              class="h-5 w-5 shrink-0 transition duration-300 group-open:-rotate-180 stroke-gray-100"
              xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
              fill="none"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              stroke-width="1.5"
            >
              <path
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                d="M19.5 8.25l-7.5 7.5-7.5-7.5"></path>
            </svg>
          </summary>

          <div class="p-4 pt-0 text-gray-300">
            <p>Open Preferences through either:</p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-5">
              <li>The Settings menu in your Mac's menubar under Blankie</li>
              <li>The titlebar menu</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group bg-dark-gray rounded-lg">
          <summary
            class="flex cursor-pointer items-center justify-between gap-1.5 p-4 text-gray-900"
          >
            <h2 class="font-medium text-gray-100">
              What's the difference between Blankie and Blanket?
            </h2>
            <svg
              class="h-5 w-5 shrink-0 transition duration-300 group-open:-rotate-180 stroke-gray-100"
              xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
              fill="none"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              stroke-width="1.5"
            >
              <path
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                d="M19.5 8.25l-7.5 7.5-7.5-7.5"></path>
            </svg>
          </summary>

          <div class="p-4 pt-0 text-gray-300">
            <p class="mb-2">
              Blankie is a native macOS app inspired by Blanket, but it's
              completely separate and independently developed:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2">
              <li>Written specifically for macOS using Swift and SwiftUI</li>
              <li>Designed to feel native on Apple Silicon and Intel Macs</li>
              <li>Built with different sound mixing and playback technology</li>
              <li>
                Independent codebase (though we use some of the same openly
                licensed sounds)
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group bg-dark-gray rounded-lg">
          <summary
            class="flex cursor-pointer items-center justify-between gap-1.5 p-4 text-gray-900"
          >
            <h2 class="font-medium text-gray-100">
              Does Blankie collect any data?
            </h2>
            <svg
              class="h-5 w-5 shrink-0 transition duration-300 group-open:-rotate-180 stroke-gray-100"
              xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
              fill="none"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              stroke-width="1.5"
            >
              <path
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                d="M19.5 8.25l-7.5 7.5-7.5-7.5"></path>
            </svg>
          </summary>

          <div class="p-4 pt-0 text-gray-300">
            <p>
              No. Blankie doesn't collect any data or connect to the internet.
              When distributed through Apple's platforms, Apple provides basic
              anonymous statistics about downloads and crashes, but the app
              itself never collects or transmits any data. See our <a
                href="/privacy"
                class="text-yellow-500 hover:text-yellow-700 transition-colors"
                >Privacy Policy</a
              > for more details.
            </p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group bg-dark-gray rounded-lg">
          <summary
            class="flex cursor-pointer items-center justify-between gap-1.5 p-4 text-gray-900"
          >
            <h2 class="font-medium text-gray-100">
              I found a bug. How do I report it?
            </h2>
            <svg
              class="h-5 w-5 shrink-0 transition duration-300 group-open:-rotate-180 stroke-gray-100"
              xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
              fill="none"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              stroke-width="1.5"
            >
              <path
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                d="M19.5 8.25l-7.5 7.5-7.5-7.5"></path>
            </svg>
          </summary>

          <div class="p-4 pt-0 text-gray-300">
            <p>
              Please open an issue on our <a
                href="https://github.com/codybrom/blankie/issues"
                class="text-yellow-500 hover:text-yellow-700 transition-colors"
                >GitHub Issues page</a
              >. Include as much detail as possible about what happened and how
              to reproduce the bug.
            </p>
          </div>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>
